&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;TripArc’s&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;goals are simple. To make our network of over 1400 travel entities more profitable, efficient and help them create truly unique travel for their clients.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;TripArc is looking for a UX Design Intern to join our Product Design team. This internship is an opportunity to gain hands-on experience designing real products used by travel professionals.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working alongside experienced UX Designers, Product Managers, and Engineers, you&#39;ll contribute to solving meaningful user problems through research, ideation, wireframing, prototyping, testing, and visual design. You&#39;ll learn how user-centered design influences product strategy while building practical experience across the entire product development lifecycle.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a member of the UX Design team, you will:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support UX Designers in research, discovery, ideation, prototyping, and usability testing activities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create wireframes, user flows, mockups, and interactive prototypes for new features and product improvements.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in user research, and helping synthesize insights.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with competitive analysis and market research to better understand user needs and industry trends.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with Product Managers, Engineers, and other designers throughout the design process.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare design documentation, presentations, and specifications for engineering handoff.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Incorporate feedback from teammates, stakeholders, and user testing into design iterations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Learn and apply UX best practices while contributing to real product initiatives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Skills We&#39;re Looking For:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Passion for creating intuitive, user-centered digital experiences.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong problem-solving and critical thinking skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Curiosity and willingness to learn from feedback and mentorship.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understanding of UX fundamentals, including user research, information architecture, interaction design, and usability principles.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to communicate ideas through sketches, wireframes, and presentations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaboration and communication skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Attention to detail and eagerness to continuously improve.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Interest in AI tools and how they can support design, research, or prototyping workflows.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
